wiki.summary: blackbear channels his frustration in the leading single off his 2017 album "digital druglord", which is an ode to a failing relationship with an evidently conceited and self-centered girl. Throughout the song, it becomes apparent that the girl in question is extremely privileged, and takes advantage of the sort of attention she receives from men – particularly rich and famous ones. The chorus is a play on the “Solfège” harmonic scale commonly used in music education to teach pitch: do, re, mi, fa, so, la, ti, do. Read more on Last.fm.
